					About 
					Hilltop Securities, Inc.  (HTS)







Hilltop Securities, Inc. (formerly 
"SWS", now "HTS") is based in Dallas, Texas and is a fully disclosed securities 
clearing firm.  HTS is a member of The New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) and regulated by the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority 
("FINRA")
 
HTS is also a member of the Securities Investors
Protection Corporation ("SIPC").  To learn more about how SIPC protects
the public investor, please visit their web site at 
www.sipc.org. 
In addition to SIPC coverage,
					Hilltop Securities, Inc. insures each customer
(as defined by SIPC).  It should be
noted that this insurance coverage protects against failure of the firm etc.,
NOT against market loss. 
 
HTS is the custodian of our clients 
assets.  What this means is your money is held at HTS. At no time should 
funds being deposited into your HTS brokerage account be made out to your rep or 
to Polar Investment Counsel, Inc.  All deposits are to be made to HIlltop 
Securities Inc., for the benefit of your account.   
For more information, 
					please visit their web site
at 
					www.hilltopsecurities.com 






				 































 
 
 
 


				 



